{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/mortons-neuroma/diagnosis/investigations/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"bae0d061-1470-55a9-a62b-af3e748e9746","slug":"investigations","fullItemName":"Investigations","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field ae7f38ad-57b7-4506-a731-d4c422c5dc13 --><h2>What investigations can help make the diagnosis of Morton's neuroma?</h2><!-- end field ae7f38ad-57b7-4506-a731-d4c422c5dc13 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 10eed1c6-0775-4d00-8bdd-2a8a1e8522ca --><!-- begin field 93907f3d-2363-4353-acf0-05d4acc78a62 --><ul><li>Morton's neuroma is essentially a clinical diagnosis and investigations are generally unnecessary.</li><li>If the diagnosis is uncertain:<ul><li>Consider arranging an X-ray to exclude other pathology such as fracture or arthropathy.</li><li>Consider checking full blood count, erythrocyte sedimentation rate, and uric acid to exclude conditions such as osteomyelitis, gout, and inflammatory arthritis.</li><li>An ultrasound scan or magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) can confirm a diagnosis of Morton's neuroma, although use of MRI is not usually necessary.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 93907f3d-2363-4353-acf0-05d4acc78a62 --><!-- end item 10eed1c6-0775-4d00-8bdd-2a8a1e8522ca -->","topic":{"id":"c4ebddd3-af48-5e8f-8ed1-2aa76e4070b1","topicId":"9c31e668-1581-468d-96ce-d99c2ab7aafd","topicName":"Morton's neuroma","slug":"mortons-neuroma","lastRevised":"Last revised in September 2016","chapters":[{"id":"6b4bc981-9cba-54b9-a87e-957a4ba57063","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"99c0e452-b2cc-5886-a9d5-42668ea2848b","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e9621e25-5b00-55db-8ce0-dac8a32d6e79","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"0778b768-ea67-588d-a616-1e8395dbc885","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"28539e40-1bb1-5637-9513-11f21e7ec437","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"7b0d11fa-c26c-56a1-b4a4-06066bd88dd5","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"1bbe8a45-c581-593c-ac16-b8ee44b7ef1c","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"c8d77046-8667-5a33-864c-7a428a7daac5","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"84bb4d88-4dc9-5852-b1f5-dc257ef000be","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"f5e1c977-5bac-5472-819c-aa3b1384131c","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"18d2ba4f-b8d8-5c6a-98de-428afdbad5d6","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"b8fdf873-b643-5040-a135-509dbf09ff0a","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"f1228408-c50d-54be-8529-51d0e559cf81","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"694e194c-a565-5187-ae74-569bcc85ff8b","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"8a77b723-1740-585c-a700-efb1ef7e8a79","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"d16d1ed5-142d-55fe-8b6e-5a521a8d9949","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"89e18e15-c3b9-50c6-9103-876d17ded2e7","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"bcc77666-f42a-5651-9873-2e5b444c221f","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"bcd4e399-0634-5e58-a78e-879494ccc88e","slug":"clinical-features","fullItemName":"Clinical features"},{"id":"bae0d061-1470-55a9-a62b-af3e748e9746","slug":"investigations","fullItemName":"Investigations"},{"id":"eda5d38f-0ac3-58e9-8451-e66d6c910ef6","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"d564918d-68a3-50a7-852a-b99cca2bfd1e","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"71b7c020-9e00-52e0-89f8-7dad624cea7a","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"3150c7ca-a619-5595-ab2a-0c6f1e29223d","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"08c23e8c-75ad-5216-88b9-844bd1219048","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"88366459-46a4-5069-990a-87594f4f055a","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"da35da28-44e3-5b98-ad77-55a820f87c55","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"a4598807-62a8-5379-a81d-f17dee67d032","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"6cabbcb4-2be8-54ac-94dd-60a42359c721","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"731a622f-9c34-59de-b09c-49032e2e130b","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"6768375b-6e33-5079-bbab-ee2de85785b9","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"bcc77666-f42a-5651-9873-2e5b444c221f","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"d1c05bed-c144-5303-bc97-2ab961885ee3","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-3d5","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d7a03f7e-19d5-462e-a252-7c32bac5774b --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field d7a03f7e-19d5-462e-a252-7c32bac5774b -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 3d52e9a8-9ab7-444a-adb2-d8a618d6df14 --><!-- begin field 8f0603ab-149a-4aeb-8098-55c61d8d1536 --><h4>Clinical diagnosis of Morton's neuroma</h4><ul><li>The recommendation that investigations are generally not necessary for Morton's neuroma as it is essentially a clinical diagnosis is based on expert opinion in a clinical consensus statement [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Thomas et al, 2009a</a>] and a review article [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Pomeroy et al, 2015</a>].</li></ul><h4>X-ray</h4><ul><li>The recommendation regarding X-ray is based on expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Adams, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Adams et al, 2011</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Peters et al, 2011</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Pomeroy et al, 2015</a>]<strong> </strong>and the expert opinion of previous reviewers of this CKS topic.</li></ul><h4>Serology</h4><ul><li>The recommendation to consider checking full blood count, erythrocyte sedimentation rate, and uric acid to exclude other painful conditions of the foot is based on expert opinion in a review article [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Coughlin, 2000</a>] and what CKS considers to be good clinical practice.</li></ul><h4>Ultrasound and magnetic resonance imaging (MRI)</h4><ul><li>Ultrasound scan and MRI are highly accurate in detecting and localizing Morton's neuroma [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Redd et al, 1989</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Zanetti and Weishaupt, 2005</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Lee et al, 2007</a>]  with high sensitivity and specificity [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Adams, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Summers, 2010</a>].</li><li>Expert opinion in a review article suggests that MRI is not usually required to make a diagnosis of Morton's neuroma [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Adams, 2010</a>] and expert opinion in a clinical consensus document advises that MRI should be reserved for certain clinical situations (for example if multiple neuromas are suspected or the presentation is atypical) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mortons-neuroma/references/\">Thomas et al, 2009a</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 8f0603ab-149a-4aeb-8098-55c61d8d1536 --><!-- end item 3d52e9a8-9ab7-444a-adb2-d8a618d6df14 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}